com.github.btrekkie.reductions.mario

Enum MarioTile

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MarioTile>
      • com.github.btrekkie.reductions.mario.MarioTile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MarioTile>

    public enum MarioTile
extends java.lang.Enum<MarioTile>
    The contents of a 1 x 1 cell in a MarioProblem. The contents of a tile may leak into other cells. For example, the castle occupies not only its own cell, but also cells above it and to the right. However, we still use just one castle tile (per castle). MarioTile objects represent movable objects such as goombas, because this representation is more useful for the purposes of MarioProblem.
